'''shebang'''
# A [[lean-to]] or temporary [[shelter]]; probably of [[Celtic]] orgin, this meaning is now lost in use, except in the expression, "there goes the whole shebang", refering to something coming completely [[apart]].
# The [[character]] [[string]] "<tt>#!</tt>" used at the beginning of a [[computer]] [[file]] to indicate which [[interpreter]] can process the [[command]]s in the file. Chiefly used in [[Unix]] and related [[operating system]]s.
